<TITLE> AL submits its amended constitution </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 21 (bdnews24.com)The ruling Awami League has submitted its amended constitution to the Election Commission after dropping the name of Swadhinata Chikitsak Parisad as an associate body and revising its section on foreign chapters to comply with electoral law. Central committee member Aminul Islam told bdnews24.com Sunday: "Swadinata Chikitsak Parisad will remain an independent organisation from now on." Bangladesh Mohila Awami League, Bangladesh Krishik League, Bangladesh Awami Jubo League, Awami Swecchasebok League, Awami Ainjibi Parisad, Bangladesh Tanti League and Bangladesh Jubo Mohila League will remain associate bodies of Awami League, he said. Jatiya Sramik League and Bangladesh Chhatra League will follow their respective constitutions. Bangladeshi expatriates who support Awami League can form organisations according to the laws of their respective countries, said Islam. The decisions were endorsed on Dec 12, he said, to ensure the party constitution complied with the Representation of the People's Order. On Nov 22, the EC wrote to Awami League informing it of the inconsistencies with the RPO. The Awami League undertook steps to correct the inconsistencies on the basis of the EC's directions. AL president Sheikh Hasina was empowered to amend the constitution of the party at its third conference on July 24. Sheikh Hasina approved the amendments after consultation with party leaders, said Islam. Islam and other party officials submitted the amended constitution to chief election commissioner ATM Shamsul Huda on Sunday. bdnew
